HEADWORD: Stoicism
<hw>Sto"i*cism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>sto⟦ium⟧cisme</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The opinions and
maxims of the Stoics.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A real or pretended indifference to pleasure or
pain; insensibility; impassiveness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stoicity</ent>⟦br⟧
